# Semgrep ignore file
# Files and directories excluded from Semgrep SAST scanning

# Template scaffolding files
# These files contain nginx configuration, Flask apps, and other service code
# as templates to be copied by users. Patterns like `proxy_set_header Host $host`
# and `app.run(host='0.0.0.0')` are intentional for their target environments
# (nginx reverse proxy and Docker containers respectively).
src/templates/

# Nginx configuration generators
# These shell scripts output nginx config via heredocs. Semgrep's nginx rules
# fire on the string content of these heredocs (which is correct nginx config),
# not on the shell code itself. The $host / $server_name patterns inside
# heredocs are nginx variables, not attacker-controlled shell variables.
src/lib/build/nginx.sh
src/lib/build/core-modules/nginx-generator.sh
src/lib/build/core-modules/nginx-setup.sh
src/lib/services/nginx-generator.sh
src/lib/ssl/ssl.sh
